TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Stochastic Model of Applied Research
AU  - Evenson, Robert E.
AU  - Kislev, Yoav
Y1  - 1976/04/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260431
DO  - 10.1086/260431
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 265
EP  - 281
VL  - 84
IS  - 2
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - A mathematical model of applied research is formulated. It views applied research as a search in a given distribution; basic research shifts the distribution searched. The productivity of applied research effort is a function of the gap between technology in practice and basic knowledge. With constant basic and applied research a (stochastic) steady state emerges in which technological change is determined by the rate of progress of basic knowledge, and the technological gap by the level of applied research.
AB  - A mathematical model of applied research is formulated. It views applied research as a search in a given distribution; basic research shifts the distribution searched. The productivity of applied research effort is a function of the gap between technology in practice and basic knowledge. With constant basic and applied research a (stochastic) steady state emerges in which technological change is determined by the rate of progress of basic knowledge, and the technological gap by the level of applied research.
