TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Model of Optimal Human-Capital Accumulation and the Wages of Young High School Graduates
AU  - Brown, Charles
Y1  - 1976/04/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260433
DO  - 10.1086/260433
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 299
EP  - 316
VL  - 84
IS  - 2
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper estimates the parameters of Ben-Porath's model of optimal accumulation of human capital over the life cycle. A discrete-time version of the model is presented, and previous estimates of its parameters are considered. Using longitudinal data on wages of young white high school graduates, these parameters are reestimated. The point estimates of the two key parameters (the discount rate and the elasticity of investment costs with respect to investments) are implausible on a priori grounds, confirming the essentially negative conclusions of earlier studies.
AB  - This paper estimates the parameters of Ben-Porath's model of optimal accumulation of human capital over the life cycle. A discrete-time version of the model is presented, and previous estimates of its parameters are considered. Using longitudinal data on wages of young white high school graduates, these parameters are reestimated. The point estimates of the two key parameters (the discount rate and the elasticity of investment costs with respect to investments) are implausible on a priori grounds, confirming the essentially negative conclusions of earlier studies.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260433
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/260433
Y2  - 2024/03/22
